cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on visual recognition tasks, specifically face recognition using light field cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes novel LSTM cell architectures for creating richer and more effective description models, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with multimedia data (light field images) and their processing, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper also discusses the computational complexity, memory efficiency, and parallelization ability of the proposed solutions, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
